title: Short Story Collection Vol. 055
creator: Various
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox’s Short Story Collection 055: a collection of 20 short works of fiction in the public domain read by a group of LibriVox members, including stories by J. M. Barrie, O. Henry, Jerome, Joyce, London, Saki, R. L. Stevenson, Trollope, Wilde and Wodehouse. For further information, including reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. This collection comprises: Tale of Sinuhe Author unknown, trans. Alan Gardiner (1879-1963) Filboid Studge by Saki (1870-1916) The Sphinx Without a Secret by Oscar Wilde (1854-1900) A Holiday in Bed by J. M. Barrie (1860-1937) The Man who Would Manage by Jerome K. Jerome (1859-1927) An Encounter by James Joyce (1882-1941) Tony's Wife from The Goodness of St Rocque by Alice Dunbar (1875-1935) (as Alice Dunbar-Nelson) That Spot Jack London (1876-1916) The Dumb Man by Sherwood Anderson (1876-1941) From the Teeth of the Tide by Charles G.D. Roberts (1860-1943) The Garden of Memories by C. A. Mercer from Atlantic Narratives - Modern short stories A Lodging For The Night by Robert Louis Stevenson (1850-1894) The Magic Shadow by Sir Arthur Thomas Quiller-Couch (1863-1944) The Gentle Euphemia by Anthony Trollope (1815-1882) The Gentle Euphemia by Anthony Trollope (1815-1882) The Clicking of Cuthbert by P. G. Wodehouse (1881-1975) The Opening of the Will by from the book: Flegeljahre by Jean Paul Richter (1763 - 1825) Translated by Frances H.King While the Auto Waits by O. Henry (1862-1910) Idyl Of London by Beatrice Harraden (1864–1936) A Walk up the Avenue by Richard Harding Davies (1864-1916) M4B format available
